  levelNumber: 19
  levelName: Uxmal
  location: "Yucat\xE1n, Mexico"
  levelDescription: "Where rain gods watched from carved stone, Uxmal rose in elegance
    and legend.\n\nUxmal, meaning \u201CThree Times Built\u201D in Maya, is one of
    the most beautiful cities of the Puuc region in Yucat\xE1n, Mexico. Flourishing
    between 600\u20131000 AD, it was a major political and ceremonial center, known
    for its distinctive Puuc architectural style\u2014smooth limestone walls decorated
    with intricate stone mosaics.\r\n\r\nThe city\u2019s most iconic structure is
    the Pyramid of the Magician, a towering oval-shaped temple tied to Maya legends.
    Uxmal also features the Nunnery Quadrangle, richly carved with masks of the rain
    god Chaac, reflecting the Maya\u2019s reliance on rainfall in this dry region.
    Other highlights include the Governor\u2019s Palace, considered one of the finest
    examples of Maya architecture, and the Great Pyramid overlooking the city.\r\n\r\nToday,
    Uxmal is a UNESCO World Heritage Site, admired for its artistry, legends, and
    the way its temples harmonize with the surrounding hills."
  siteImage: {fileID: 21300000, guid: 71e3ba860b4ad3b4ba41ad083846654f, type: 3}
